{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:52:11.713890+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have a complete picture. Here's what needs to be done:\n\n1. **`docs/troubleshooting.md`** already exists with just placeholder text. I need to flesh it out with meaningful troubleshooting content.\n2. **`mkdocs.yml`** is missing the troubleshooting page in the `nav` section. I need to add it.\n\nThe validation script checks that required files exist and that `mkdocs.yml` has `site_name:` and `nav:` — my changes won't break either check.\n\nLet me implement both changes in a single commit:", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1087, "prompt_tokens": 9648, "total_tokens": 10735, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 536, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9280, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.001139178, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.000193488, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00094569}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780865513-Hj1eoLyt3zkfHpFPCq4k", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3db-3617-71a2-906c-3437780bf775-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "push_files", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T16_R01_C02_A01", "branch": "main", "message": "Add troubleshooting documentation and include it in MkDocs nav", "files": [{"path": "docs/troubleshooting.md", "content": "# Troubleshooting\n\nThis page covers common issues encountered when building or serving the documentation site.\n\n## MkDocs build fails with configuration error\n\nEnsure `mkdocs.yml` contains valid YAML and defines both `site_name` and `nav`. Run `mkdocs build --strict` to surface warnings as errors.\n\n## Missing pages in the navigation\n\nEvery Markdown file referenced in `nav` must exist under the `docs/` directory. Verify the path matches the filename exactly, including any subdirectory prefix (for example, `api/overview.md`).\n\n## Broken internal links\n\nUse relative links without a leading slash (for example, `[Configuration](configuration.md)`). MkDocs resolves these relative to the current page at build time.\n\n## Python dependency issues\n\nInstall project dependencies with:\n\n```bash\npip install -r requirements.txt\n```\n\nIf you still encounter errors, confirm you are using Python 3.8 or later.\n\n## Validation command reports errors\n\nRun the repository validator:\n\n```bash\nmake validate\n```\n\nAddress any errors listed before submitting a pull request.\n"}, {"path": "mkdocs.yml", "content": "site_name: Clean MkDocs Benchmark\nsite_description: Documentation benchmark repository\nnav:\n  - Home: index.md\n  - Getting Started: getting-started.md\n  - Configuration: configuration.md\n  - Troubleshooting: troubleshooting.md\n  - API:\n      - Overview: api/overview.md\n      - Errors: api/errors.md\ntheme:\n  name: material\nmarkdown_extensions:\n  - admonition\n"}]}, "id": "call_b063131717f041f5b69832f0", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9648, "output_tokens": 1087, "total_tokens": 10735, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9280}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 536}}}}]}}}
